Ghana attracted $552.3 million in
foreign direct investment in the second quarter, the Ghana
Investment Promotion Centre said in a statement handed to
reporters today in Accra, the capital.  The West African country received $351.8 million in
investment in the first quarter, the agency said in April.  To contact the reporter on this story:
